{
  "doc_id": "16152",
  "text": "We conclude that the theory presented in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] does not represent a significant improvement over analysis methods used so far. In fact, a good approximation [CITATION_3] to the full theory is equivalent to the theory of Winther and Alder [CITATION_4] , which is widely used in the analysis of CE data at high beam energies. We furthermore conclude that the large differences of up to 30% reported in [CITATION_5] are likely solely due to an interchange of center-of-mass and laboratory angles and the use of incident beam energy instead of the mid-target beam energy in the calculation of the CE cross sections.",
